{
  "_id": "lotmAbilityR8002",
  "name": "Annotated Procedure",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-bound-black-brown.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Baseline (1 Spirituality):</strong> As a bonus action, open a structured annotation protocol for 10 minutes (concentration). Choose one studied topic (rituals, contracts, historical records, occult symbols, or technical schematics). While active, you have advantage on Arcana, History, Religion, and Investigation checks directly related to that topic. The first ritual you complete during the duration may either reduce preparation time by 5 minutes (minimum 1 minute) or reduce ritual spirituality surcharge by 1 (minimum 0).</p><p><strong>Higher Spend (upcast):</strong></p><ul><li><strong>+1 Spirituality:</strong> Duration becomes 1 hour and one ally within 30 feet gains the same check advantage while they can hear your instructions.</li><li><strong>+2 Spirituality:</strong> During one ritual this duration, ignore one mundane interruption that would normally force re-setup (noise, jostling, weather shift, or misplaced component).</li><li><strong>+4 Spirituality:</strong> During one ritual this duration, apply both baseline benefits (time reduction and surcharge reduction), and encode a 1-paragraph private notation that requires a check against your spell save DC to decipher.</li></ul><p><em>Counterplay:</em> Destroyed notes, silence effects, or anti-magic suppression can break concentration and end the protocol.</p><p><em>Corruption Hook:</em> If you knowingly endanger bystanders to preserve a ritual optimization created by this ability, gain 1 Corruption.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
